byline.contributor: Julie Turkewitz reported from Colorado Springs, and Ashley Southall from New York. Jack Healy and Dave Philipps contributed reporting from Colorado Springs.
byline.original: By JULIE TURKEWITZ and ASHLEY SOUTHALL

abstract: Colorado Springs sheriff’s department identifies 29-year-old army veteran Ke’Arre M Stewart and 35-year-old mother Jennifer Markovsky as two additional victims in fatal shooting at local Planned Parenthood clinic.
lead_paragraph: Ke’Arre M. Stewart, a former Army specialist, and Jennifer Markovsky, the wife of an Army veteran, were killed along with a police officer, Garrett Swasey.

headline.main: Colorado Victims Identified as Iraq Veteran and Woman From Hawaii
headline.print_headline: Two Victims Identified, One an Iraq War Veteran, Both With Military Ties
